<p class="faq-question">
Emergency Response Plan
<p class="faq-answer">
In the event of severe weather/lightning detected in the Village after 9:00am, or severe weather/lightning predicted in the Village during the parade hours, the event will be cancelled. Should the event be cancelled, River Forest Police will notify all residents on the parade route, and the River Forest Park District will be responsible notify all parade participants in the staging area.
<ol>
<li> The River Forest Park District will make a cancellation announcement via PA system. The River Forest Park District has also created an Emergency Contact list of all entries and will call parade contacts. Parade contacts should have their cell phones with them and powered on the morning of the parade.
</li>
<li> Parade Cancellations will be posted on the River Forest Park Distrct rain hotline at <a href="tel://1-708-802-1314">708 802 1314</a>.
</li>
<li> Feel free to call Karen Stiles, Superintendent of Recreation, at <a href="tel://1-847-951-1058">847 951 1058</a> or Mike Sletten, Executive Director at <a href="tel://1-708-890-1092">708 890 1092</a>.
</li>
